    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-10-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <head>407. Memorandum From the Secretary of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WBGRD1" type="from">Wentworth</persName>) to the Chairman of the
                    Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName corresp="#p_RAAW1" type="to"
                        >Radford</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d407fn1">Source:
                            <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Records, OCJCS 091 Palestine (Jun
                        56–Dec 56). Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Actions with respect to the Middle East
                        Situation agreed upon at <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Meeting 29
                        October 1956<note n="2" xml:id="d407fn2">
                            <p>According to the history prepared by the <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                                    >JCS</gloss> Historical Office, this meeting was held shortly
                                after the Israeli Government issued its communiqué concerning the
                                invasion of Sinai. (See “The Suez Canal Crisis”, <ref
                                    target="#pg_19">pp. 19</ref>–<ref target="#pg_20">20</ref>,
                                Chapter X in <hi rend="italic">The Joint Chiefs of Staff and
                                    National Security, 1953–1956</hi>; <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                                    >JCS</gloss> Historical Office Files)</p>
                            <p>At 6:43 p.m. on October 29, <persName corresp="#p_RWM1"
                                    >Rountree</persName> telephoned <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                                    >Dulles</persName> and informed him of most of the measures
                                described in this memorandum. <persName corresp="#p_RWM1"
                                    >Rountree</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                                    >Dulles</persName> that they were decisions taken by the Navy
                                and that he had learned of them from <persName>Herbert D.
                                    Riley</persName> of Admiral <persName corresp="#p_BAWF1"
                                    >Boone</persName>’s office. (Memorandum of telephone
                                conversation by <persName corresp="#p_BPD1">Bernau</persName>;
                                Eisenhower Library, Dulles Papers, General Telephone
                                Conversations)</p>
                        </note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>At their meeting on 29 October 1956 the Joint Chiefs of Staff agreed to take the
                    following actions with respect to the Middle East situation: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="italic">General</hi>.</p>
                            <p>Dispatch a message to all unified commanders outlining the present
                                situation, including the latest Watch Committee report, and
                                informing them of actions being taken by the <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                                    >JCS</gloss>.</p>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Army</hi>. <list>
                                <label>a.</label>
                                <item>Alert one regimental combat team in Europe for possible
                                    movement.</item>
                                <label>b.</label>
                                <item>Alert one regimental combat team from the Continental United
                                    States for possible movement.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Navy</hi>. <list>
                                <label>a.</label>
                                <item>Direct <gloss target="#t_CINCNELM1">CINCNELM</gloss> to
                                    establish command headquarters on the U.S.S. <hi rend="italic"
                                        >Pocono</hi> by 2 November 1956. (Defense and State
                                    clearance required.)</item>
                                <label>b.</label>
                                <item>Order one hunter killer group<note n="3" xml:id="d407fn3">A
                                        naval unit equipped for anti-submarine warfare.</note>
                                    (consisting of one <gloss target="#t_CVS1">CVS</gloss>, six DD,
                                    and two <gloss target="#t_SS2">SS</gloss>) from the west coast
                                    of Europe (Rotterdam) into the Mediterranean, to report to
                                    Commander, Sixth Fleet. (Defense and State clearance
                                    required.)</item>
                                <label>c.</label>
                                <item>Cancel Sixth Fleet participation in <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                                        >NATO</gloss> exercise “Beehive”, and order carrier strike
                                    force to positions east and southeast of Cyprus and within six
                                    hours’ sailing distance of Cyprus.</item>
                                <label>d.</label>
                                <item>Cancel the amphibious exercise in the Atlantic and issue
                                    instructions to plan for loading out one Marine battalion
                                    landing team.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="0867" n="827" xml:id="pg_827"/>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Air Force</hi>. <list>
                                <label>a.</label>
                                <item>Alert one C–124 wing in the Continental United States for
                                    movement to the Middle East.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Marine Corps</hi>. <list>
                                <label>a.</label>
                                <item>Alert one battalion landing team in the Continental United
                                    States for possible movement to the Middle East.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WBGRD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Wentworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
